No. No. Definitely not. Definitely not. In fact - if - anybody come to visit us and there's adults talking there we were out of the room. We weren't a
llowed to - chip in an all that. That's why - my eldest - daughter in America now - she - is bringing her children up - the same way as they bring them up here. The American child - they do join in. See? But - my daughter won't have none of that. Oh no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 
