t presents. Yes. Get a present from mother and - generally the - sisters if - they didn't have enough they'd club up together and buy a present and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 
Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day? How would you -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4860835 BR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 
No, that would - that was one day when all - the family - were - mother, dad and children, all sat down - 'course we'd - go to church when - at - when we were small like, and that. But our mother didn't go to church, she was - sent us - to church
 and that. Dad would never go to church. The only time dad went to church was funerals and weddings. You see and the same - I - I - I'm the same way now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 Would your mother ever go?
