she didn't have - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6512867\charrsid6384043 she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043  didn't have a lot of time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 But she sent you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4860835 BR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 Oh yes, she - we had to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 Would she go with you on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4860835 BR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 No. No. No, she'd be - yes, she'd be too busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 What did you do then on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4860835 BR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 
Oh go round our friends houses and all that. That's another thing - as regards this - particular area. You never used to see the doors shut, even - it - must be very very bad weather, but in summertime - all the doors round here were open. Of a Christ
mastime - we used to have - guitars and mandolins and all that and we'd go from house to house - if we felt like a drink we could have a drink just - just wish them a merry Christmas, onto the next place and all round the streets. We used to have dancing 
i
n the street - to - in the summer - time, 'til two or three in the morning. And I can remember - when we were playing that - like on the corner say of - we generally used to get on the corner of Angelina Street - and - and - Maria Street. We could play th
e
re, and - see - the policeman - stood up in the doorway on - corner of say Nelson Street. And he'd be stood up there say for - about twenty minutes quarter of an hour, then he'd walk down slowly, he'd say, now come on boys, break it up. There were boys an
d
 girls all dancing in the road and - you know, and he'd say, come on - break it up now. All right - because we used to know all the policemen then. There was - Phipps and - oh - Jessie Hayes - were a lot of - different policemen we used to know. All right
 
officer. And we'd walk down a - and we'd walk down, there were seven of us used to play, and we'd walk down to the - corner and that without playing, 'course the policeman think to himself - he's gone on - and that, he wouldn't trouble us again. We'd go -
 get back on the other corner and start playing. 'Course they all knew the dodges and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 What were the police like down here then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4860835 BR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 
Yes. Very good. I think - compared to the police of today - they were more - family concerned, in this respect that
 - if they caught a boy - like - deliberately throwing stones, breaking a window - they'd turn round and flip him across the earhole, and - we wouldn't do it again, you know - or - they used to do - at one time they used to do - fellows and that they used
 to do a lot of - gathering on the corner - and that. And perhaps - one or two of the young fellows get there - and if a policeman caught 'em - give 'em such a smack, he wouldn't summons 'em, but they used to cure 'em, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 Were they around here, do yo
u remember one near where you were living when you were a boy police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4860835 BR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 
I - do I remember? Well when we were living in Maria Street the - the - police station was on the corner of Maria Street, Bute Street and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 Were you frightened of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4860835 BR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 We respected 'em. Yes, we res - we respected 'em. - Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4860835 BR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 I used to play a mandolin and guitar. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7556174 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5248227\charrsid6384043 Any of the rest of you play?
